Rating: 4
I agree with other reviewers. This was hands down the best prime rib ever, but it was quite rare as we had a very large roast (9lbs). If you're going to invest in an expensive piece of meat, get a GOOD roasting thermometer. The mustard seeds singed and the onions did dry out a bit too much as well. Lower heat and longer cooking time. The horseradish cream was amazing, but I could have halved the recipe as the meat was so flavorful, everyone only needed a spoonful and they are serious horseradish fans. It was a waste to throw away the rest of the cream when the meat was clearly polished off. I will most definitely make this again!

Rating: 0
The creme fraiche was wonderful and I followed the horseradish-mustard sauce exactly, and it was a hit! So was the au jus (so easy!). No packages for me. Prime rib mouth watering, but good thing we all liked it rare, because it really could have used a bit more cooking - I'd go with 125 or 130 degrees instead of 120 next time. Definitely the best prime rib I've ever done.

