Rating: 4
We made this for Christmas. It was great. I didn't have any problem with the mustard or onions burning or browning too much. We'll be making this again. The gravy was so good that we made some mashed potatoes the next day to use the gravy up.

Rating: 4
Every part of this recipe was great. The dijon was a really nice addition to a traditional horseradish cream. I might add just a little more horseradish next time just because my family really likes it. The roast turned out perfect and the mustard seeds didn't blacken at all, but adding the whole grain mustard is a great idea. The onions and jus were a huge hit. I will definitely make this again!

Rating: 3
The dijon-horseradish creme was a highlight. The roast tasted great, but the mustard-garlic rub was too blackened before the internal temperature of the roast reached 120 degrees. Also, the onions could probably use a more oil to keep from crisping black or certainly require more mixing during the roasting. I would do this again, but probably at a lower temperature for longer to preserve the crust on the roast and carmelize the onions.

Rating: 4
I just made this for Christmas dinner to rave reviews. I didn't use the yellow mustard seeds, but instead added about a tablespoon of whole grain mustard to the dijon/garlic rub. Everyone thought the jus was fabulous and the onions even better. Great holiday treat!

